com.magnet.android.mms.utils.logger

Class LogDumper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.magnet.android.mms.utils.logger.LogDumper

  • public class LogDumper
extends Object
    This class dumps the Android logcat entries bounded by a process. It filters the log by process ID's, and does not filter them by tags. This utility class heavily depends on the output format of logcat, and requires the android.permission.READ_LOGS permission.

      • dump

        public static int dump(String format,
       Writer out)
        Dump the logcat entries for the current process. Each line of the log is terminated by LF.
        Parameters:
        format - The log format: FORMAT_BRIEF, FORMAT_PROCESS, FORMAT_THREADTIME, FORMAT_THREAD, FORMAT_TIME
        out - Output writer for the log entries.
        Returns:
        Number of records found, or -1 if an error occurred.
        See Also:

       int pid,

        Parameters:
        format - The log format: FORMAT_BRIEF, FORMAT_PROCESS, FORMAT_THREADTIME, FORMAT_THREAD, FORMAT_TIME
        pid - A PID whose value is greater than 0.

      • dump

        public static int dump(String format,
       int[] pids,
       Writer out)
        Dump the logcat entries for a set of process IDs or all processes. Each line of the log is terminated by a newline.
        Parameters:
        format - The log format: FORMAT_BRIEF, FORMAT_PROCESS, FORMAT_THREADTIME, FORMAT_THREAD, FORMAT_TIME
        pids - null for all processes, or an array of PIDs.
        out - Output writer for the log entries.
        Returns:
        Number of records found, or -1 if an error occurred.
        See Also:
        getPids(String)

      • getLatestPid

        public static int getLatestPid(String tag)
        Get the latest process ID for a tag.
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag used in "logcat tag:priority".
        Returns:

      • getPids

        public static int[] getPids(String tag)
        Get all process IDs for a tag. The PIDs are in the order in which log entries were inserted.
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag used in "logcat tag:priority".
        Returns:
        null for errors, an empty array if no tag found, or an array of PIDs.
